# 🖥️ COMMAND: show
Description: Displays information about the current session, environment, and loaded modules.

Usage:
    show                - List all currently set dynamic session variables.
    show options        - Display required and optional parameters for the loaded module.
    show targets        - Display the internal target database and discovered assets.
    show details        - Display specific metadata/details for the active exploit.
    show aliases        - List all configured command aliases.
    show shells         - Display available system shells from /etc/shells.
    show <VAR>          - Show the value of a specific variable (e.g., 'show R_HOST').